description:
&lt;p&gt;We have recently been awarded a 10 year contract for Adult Community Health Services across Bristol, North Somerset &amp; South Gloucestershire (BNSSG) which is a really exciting opportunity for us in Sirona care &amp; health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The growth and development of Sirona is a new and exciting chapter. This will enable us, together with our colleagues across the system, to work with individuals, carers and families to transform out-of-hospital services to support people to live longer and healthier lives, accessing care and support close to where they live and ensure consistency and equity across BNSSG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are working towards setting up Integrated Network Teams (INT) aligned to Primary care networks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be 18 INTs across BNSSG. These teams will be fully integrated ‘out of hospital’ health care services, delivered in close collaboration with primary and social care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These teams will support and empower people to stay and age well, reduce the demand for emergency hospital services and long term care placements. Integrated multidisciplinary teams, offer both planned and unplanned interventions to improve outcomes for service users and support more people to self-care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each INT will be made up of the following;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Community Matrons/Advanced Care Practitioners - Long term conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered nursing &amp; therapy professionals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly skilled support staff including nurse associates, assistant practitioners and support workers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Public health nursing (Active Ageing service)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated administrators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Integrated network teams will offer a consistent service from 8am to 8pm, 7 days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you clapped for us in April then we want you to come join us and help support our community, these are all new posts due to extra funding as the fight continues over winter…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about delivering exceptional community-based therapy, allowing service users to improve their quality of life and optimise their function? Are you committed to a Home First ethos, where people can rehabilitate and recover in their own environment, optimising their physical and emotional wellbeing? If the answer is YES, then please apply now!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking enthusiastic and innovative Occupational Therapists to provide exceptional therapy intervention to patients in their place of residence. This will include work to facilitate patients to return home from an acute stay, work to prevent admission for a patient in crisis and to undertake domiciliary therapy to prevent decline and functional deterioration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide support and guidance to support staff, students and other therapists, so will be required to demonstrate good communication and be motivated to support others in their professional development. You will be supported in your own development by our experienced senior team, with access to regular training, that is both clinical and non-clinical e.g. leadership skills in nature.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good team working, time management and the ability to take initiative are also required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have full and part time hours available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please read the full job description and if you have questions then please do get in touch with Jayrah - sirona.recruitment@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
